# Translation and Adaptation Models

!!! note "How to read model answers"
    Model answers should be analysed, not memorised. Compare them against your own draft to identify improvements in structure, evidence handling, terminology, and documentary usefulness.

## Italian-source idea

â€œAbbiamo verificato il componente e sembra tutto a posto, ma conviene fare un ulteriore controllo in seguito.â€

## Weak direct translation

> We checked the component and everything seems okay, but it is convenient to do another control later.

## Professionally adapted version

> The component was inspected and no immediate anomaly was identified. However, additional verification is recommended at a later stage in order to confirm the current assessment under repeat conditions.

## Why the adaptation is better

The adapted version removes literal interference from Italian, replaces vague wording with document-friendly phrasing, and introduces a clearer relationship between current status and follow-up recommendation.

## Premium note

Technical translation is often less about translating word by word and more about transferring **document function**, **evidence level**, and **register discipline**.

